\newlabel{tab:narration}{{14}{26}{Narration decomposition (Claude Sonnet~4.6, 100 tasks): visual+ASR (no narration) $\to $ narration-discarded $\to $ full. The discarded run isolates the inference-time articulation effect, and the gap to full isolates persistence. Per-family rows are descriptive (single-trial). Note Transient reads $9{\to }4{\to }9$, a decoding fluctuation on a 10-task cell that the totals average out.\relax }{table.caption.24}{}}
